  "text": "Radar systems have long taken advantage of bandwidth as a resource to encode range to a target in either the time domain or frequency domain. Related work has examined the localization capabilities of linear frequency modulated (LFM) continuous wave (CW) signals with RFID tags [CITATION_1] , or communication for a single active RF tag [CITATION_2] . In this work, the FMCW radar technique is utilized to take advantage of bandwidth for two purposes: 1) estimating the range from the radar to multiple sensors in the presence of multipath clutter and 2) separating signals from multiple sensors in view for simultaneous data uplink.",
